content:
How can environmental factors, such as air quality, water purity, and proximity to nature, impact physical and mental well-being based on age, gender, genetic predisposition, and pre-existing medical conditions? Please provide 5 recommendations in JSON data format. 
{
  "age": "55",
  "gender": "male",
  "genetic_predisposition": "family history of lung cancer",
  "pre_existing_medical_conditions": ["high blood pressure", "depression"],
  "recommendations": [
    {
      "type": "air quality",
      "description": "Install air purifiers and avoid outdoor activities during times of high air pollution levels to reduce the risk of respiratory complications."
    },
    {
      "type": "water purity",
      "description": "Install a water filtration system and avoid consuming contaminated water sources to reduce the risk of illnesses such as kidney disease."
    },
    {
      "type": "nature exposure",
      "description": "Spend time in natural settings such as parks or forests to improve mental well-being and reduce stress levels."
    },
    {
      "type": "screenings",
      "description": "Schedule regular health screenings for conditions such as lung cancer and high blood pressure to monitor and manage any pre-existing medical conditions."
    },
    {
      "type": "sleep",
      "description": "Prioritize getting at least 7-9 hours of quality sleep per night to support overall physical and mental health, as poor air quality and high stress levels can interfere with sleep quality."
    }
  ]
}

```json
{
  "age": "55",
  "gender": "male",
  "genetic_predisposition": "family history of lung cancer",
  "pre_existing_medical_conditions": ["high blood pressure", "depression"],
  "recommendations": [
    {
      "type": "air quality",
      "description": "Install air purifiers in your home and monitor local air quality indices. Limit outdoor activities during high pollution days to prevent respiratory issues and reduce lung cancer risk."
    },
    {
      "type": "water purity",
      "description": "Use a high-quality water filtration system to ensure the purity of drinking water. This can help protect against potential contaminants that may exacerbate conditions like high blood pressure."
    },
    {
      "type": "nature exposure",
      "description": "Engage in regular visits to green spaces, such as parks or botanical gardens, to enhance mental health and alleviate symptoms of depression. Nature exposure has been shown to lower stress and improve mood."
    },
    {
      "type": "screenings",
      "description": "Undergo periodic medical screenings to monitor lung health, blood pressure, and mental health status. Early detection and management are crucial for conditions with genetic predispositions."
    },
    {
      "type": "sleep",
      "description": "Establish a consistent sleep routine, aiming for 7-9 hours per night. Good sleep hygiene can mitigate the negative effects of stress and poor air quality, promoting better mental and physical health."
